&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;ADVERT FOR STONEHOUSE&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stonehouse ward are keen to welcome the final member of their ward nursing team!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stonehouse have a friendly team of both experienced and new nurses. We specialise in Colorectal &amp; Hepatobiliary surgery for planned and emergency patients. We offer the opportunity to gain experience in the higher dependency level 1 area that are located centrally on the ward. We are also very fortunate to be nursing in partnership with the military that support our ward with their wealth of varied experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pledge to support you through a robust training programme tailored to your individual needs &amp; interests.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a dedicated surgical clinical educator and a large team of sisters ready to buddy up with you&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We advise any interested applicants to pop in and have an informal walk around the area to meet Sister &amp; chat with our friendly team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Senior Sister Angela Evans on &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;a.evans10&lt;/span&gt;@nhs.net or (01752) 430052&lt;/p&gt;
